      <a href="https://book.douban.com/review/3734349/" class="title-link">沉浮与枯荣</a>
      <div class="toggle_review right">        <a href="javascript:;" id="toggle-3734349"class="indicator unfold j" title="展开全文">        </a>
      </div>
    </h3>
    

<div class="header-more">
    <a class="author-avatar" href="https://www.douban.com/people/4010724/"><img width="48" height="48" src="https://img3.doubanio.com/icon/u4010724-4.jpg"></a>
    <a href="https://www.douban.com/people/4010724/" class="author">
      <span property="v:reviewer">venokerlin</span>
    </a>    <span property="v:rating" class="allstar50 main-title-rating" title="力荐"></span>
  <span property="v:dtreviewed" content="2010-09-25"
      class="main-meta">2010-09-25 22:59:04</span>
</div>

  </header>

        <div class="main-bd">
          <div id="review_3734349_short" class="review-short">
            <div class="short-content">
                      人类最早的历史就是先民们口述的历史。在远古时期，老人在群体中德高望重，因为他们的生命所经历的就是历史。老人们将这一生所经历的事情告诉年轻人，一代又一代传递下去。人类的文明就是这样开始延续的。在如今的这个社会，也许人们已经不愿意再听老人口述的历史，众多的...

                    <a class="pl" href="https://book.douban.com/review/3734349/#comments">(3回应)</a>
